// Game: Postretro
// Format: Standard
// DEMO MAP — M10 entity health + damage runtime AND M10 enemy AI / pathfinding.
// Floor plan (top-down; x is east, y is north; interior x 0..512, y 0..256,
// floor z=0, ceiling z=128). Two full-height interior walls split the room into
// three bays joined by OFFSET doorways, so the enemy must route around corners
// to reach the player -- the straight line between them is blocked.
// Legend: # = wall, . = floor, P = player_spawn, E = reference_enemy, d = dummy.
//   y=256  ......................................................
//          ...........#.............BAY.2.....#................E.
//          ..P..d.....#..door.A..............#####.door.B......
//          .....d.....#...(top.gap)...........#................
//          .....d.....#..WALL.A..............WALL.B............
//          .....d.....#######.....(bottom.gap)#................
//   y=0    ......................................................
//          x=0       176 192        320 336              512
// WALL A: x[176,192] y[0,176]  -- doorway is the y[176,256] gap (TOP, ~80 wide).
// WALL B: x[320,336] y[80,256] -- doorway is the y[0,80] gap (BOTTOM, ~80 wide).
// Route: P up through door A, across BAY 2, down through door B, to E.
// Toggle the nav overlay in-game with Alt+Shift+N.
// Compile: cargo run -p postretro-level-compiler -- content/dev/maps/combat-demo.map -o content/dev/maps/combat-demo.prl
// Run:     cargo run -p postretro -- content/dev/maps/combat-demo.prl
// Toggle the nav overlay in-game with Alt+Shift+N.
// See content/dev/maps/combat-demo.README.md for what to look for.
